#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:348
msgid "How Amortization Works"
msgstr "상각 작동 방식"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:351
msgid ""
"Amortization spreads your loan into fixed payments over time. Each payment "
"includes both principal and interest."
msgstr "상각은 시간이 지남에 따라 대출금을 고정 지불액으로 분산시킵니다. 각 지불에는 원금과 이자가 모두 포함됩니다."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:355
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:466
msgid "Early payments are mostly interest"
msgstr "조기지불은 대부분 이자"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:359
msgid "Later payments are mostly principal"
msgstr "후불은 대부분 원금입니다"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:363
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_payoff_calculator.html:474
msgid "Extra payments reduce principal directly"
msgstr "추가납부로 원금이 직접 감소"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:375
msgid "Benefits of Extra Payments"
msgstr "추가 지불의 이점"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:378
msgid "Making extra payments can significantly reduce the cost of your loan:"
msgstr "추가 지불을 하면 대출 비용을 크게 줄일 수 있습니다."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:382
msgid "Save thousands in interest"
msgstr "수천 달러의 이자를 절약하세요"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:386
msgid "Pay off your mortgage years earlier"
msgstr "몇 년 전에 주택담보대출금을 갚으세요."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:390
msgid "Build home equity faster"
msgstr "주택 자산을 더 빠르게 구축하세요"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:407
msgid "Why does more of my payment go to interest at first?"
msgstr "처음에는 지불금 중 더 많은 금액이 이자로 들어가는 이유는 무엇입니까?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:408
msgid ""
"Interest is calculated on your remaining balance. When your balance is "
"highest (at the beginning), the interest charge is also highest."
msgstr "이자는 남은 잔액을 기준으로 계산됩니다. 잔고가 가장 높을 때(초기) 부과되는 이자도 가장 높습니다."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:411
msgid "When is the best time to make extra payments?"
msgstr "추가 지불을 하기 가장 좋은 시기는 언제입니까?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:412
msgid ""
"The earlier, the better! Extra payments in the first years have the greatest"
" impact since they reduce principal that would otherwise accrue interest."
msgstr "빠르면 빠를수록 좋습니다! 첫 해에 추가 지불을 하면 이자가 발생하는 원금이 줄어들기 때문에 가장 큰 영향을 미칩니다."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:415
msgid "How do I read the amortization schedule?"
msgstr "상각 일정을 어떻게 읽나요?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:416
msgid ""
"Each row shows one payment: the date, total payment amount, how much goes to"
" principal vs interest, and remaining balance after that payment."
msgstr "각 행에는 날짜, 총 결제 금액, 원금 대 이자에 대한 금액, 결제 후 남은 잔액 등 한 번의 결제가 표시됩니다."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/mortgage_amortization_calculator.html:429
