#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:349
msgid "What is GFR?"
msgstr "GFR이란 무엇입니까?"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:351
msgid ""
"GFR (Glomerular Filtration Rate) is a measure of how well your kidneys are "
"filtering waste from your blood. It represents the rate at which fluid is "
"filtered through the glomeruli (tiny filters in the kidneys) per unit of "
"time."
msgstr ""
"GFR(사구체 여과율)은 신장이 혈액에서 노폐물을 얼마나 잘 걸러내는지를 측정하는 것입니다. 이는 단위 시간당 체액이 사구체(신장에 있는"
" 작은 필터)를 통해 여과되는 속도를 나타냅니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:354
msgid ""
"eGFR (estimated GFR) is calculated using formulas that take into account "
"your creatinine level, age, gender, and race. It's expressed in milliliters "
"per minute per 1.73 square meters of body surface area (mL/min/1.73m²)."
msgstr ""
"eGFR(예상 GFR)은 크레아티닌 수준, 연령, 성별 및 인종을 고려한 공식을 사용하여 계산됩니다. 신체 표면적 1.73제곱미터당 분당"
" 밀리리터(mL/min/1.73m²)로 표시됩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:360
msgid "Why GFR is Important"
msgstr "GFR이 중요한 이유"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:362
msgid ""
"GFR is the best overall indicator of kidney function. It helps healthcare "
"providers:"
msgstr "GFR은 신장 기능에 대한 가장 좋은 종합 지표입니다. 이는 의료 서비스 제공자에게 다음과 같은 도움을 줍니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:365
msgid "Detect kidney disease early"
msgstr "신장질환을 조기에 발견하세요"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:366
msgid "Monitor kidney function over time"
msgstr "시간 경과에 따른 신장 기능 모니터링"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:367
msgid "Determine the stage of chronic kidney disease (CKD)"
msgstr "만성 신장 질환(CKD)의 단계를 결정합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:368
msgid "Make decisions about treatment and medication dosing"
msgstr "치료 및 약물 투여에 대한 결정을 내립니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:369
msgid "Assess the risk of kidney disease progression"
msgstr "신장 질환 진행 위험 평가"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:377
msgid "Enter your age (18-100 years)"
msgstr "나이(18~100세)를 입력하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:378
msgid "Select your gender (male or female)"
msgstr "성별(남성 또는 여성)을 선택하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:379
msgid "Select your race (used for formula adjustment)"
msgstr "인종을 선택하세요(공식 조정에 사용됨)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:380
msgid "Choose your creatinine unit (mg/dL or μmol/L)"
msgstr "크레아티닌 단위(mg/dL 또는 μmol/L)를 선택하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:381
msgid "Enter your serum creatinine level from your blood test"
msgstr "혈액 검사에서 얻은 혈청 크레아티닌 수치를 입력하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:382
msgid "Click 'Calculate eGFR' to see your results"
msgstr "결과를 보려면 'eGFR 계산'을 클릭하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:383
msgid "Review your eGFR value, CKD stage, and kidney function assessment"
msgstr "eGFR 값, CKD 단계 및 신장 기능 평가를 검토하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:392
msgid "eGFR Value"
msgstr "eGFR 값"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:394
msgid ""
"Your estimated glomerular filtration rate in mL/min/1.73m². Higher values "
"indicate better kidney function. Normal eGFR is typically 90 or higher."
msgstr ""
"예상 사구체 여과율(mL/min/1.73m²)입니다. 값이 높을수록 신장 기능이 향상되었음을 나타냅니다. 정상 eGFR은 일반적으로 90"
" 이상입니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:398
msgid "CKD Stage"
msgstr "CKD단계"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:400
msgid ""
"Your chronic kidney disease stage based on your eGFR value. Stages range "
"from Stage 1 (normal/high) to Stage 5 (kidney failure)."
msgstr "eGFR 값을 기준으로 한 만성 신장 질환 단계. 단계는 1단계(정상/높음)부터 5단계(신부전)까지 다양합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:404
msgid "CKD-EPI vs MDRD"
msgstr "CKD-EPI 대 MDRD"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:406
msgid ""
"The calculator shows results from both formulas. CKD-EPI is the preferred "
"formula as it's more accurate, especially at higher eGFR levels. MDRD is "
"shown for comparison."
msgstr ""
"계산기는 두 수식의 결과를 모두 표시합니다. CKD-EPI는 특히 더 높은 eGFR 수준에서 더 정확하기 때문에 선호되는 공식입니다. "
"비교를 위해 MDRD가 표시됩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:414
msgid "Chronic Kidney Disease Stages Explained"
msgstr "만성 신장 질환 단계 설명"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:417
msgid "Stage 1 (eGFR ≥ 90)"
msgstr "1단계(eGFR ≥ 90)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:419
msgid ""
"Normal or high kidney function. May have kidney damage but function is "
"preserved. Regular monitoring recommended."
msgstr "정상 또는 높은 신장 기능. 신장이 손상될 수 있지만 기능은 보존됩니다. 정기적인 모니터링을 권장합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:423
msgid "Stage 2 (eGFR 60-89)"
msgstr "2단계(eGFR 60-89)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:425
msgid ""
"Mildly decreased kidney function. Kidney damage with mild loss of function. "
"Monitoring and lifestyle changes recommended."
msgstr "신장 기능이 약간 감소했습니다. 경미한 기능 상실을 동반한 신장 손상. 모니터링 및 생활방식 변화를 권장합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:429
msgid "Stage 3a (eGFR 45-59)"
msgstr "3a기(eGFR 45-59)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:431
msgid ""
"Mildly to moderately decreased kidney function. More frequent monitoring and"
" may need to see a nephrologist."
msgstr "신장 기능이 경미하거나 중등도로 저하됩니다. 더 자주 모니터링하고 신장 전문의를 만나야 할 수도 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:435
msgid "Stage 3b (eGFR 30-44)"
msgstr "3b기(eGFR 30-44)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:437
msgid ""
"Moderately to severely decreased kidney function. Regular nephrologist "
"visits and treatment planning recommended."
msgstr "신장 기능이 중등도에서 심각하게 저하됩니다. 정기적인 신장 전문의 방문 및 치료 계획을 세우는 것이 좋습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:441
msgid "Stage 4 (eGFR 15-29)"
msgstr "4단계(eGFR 15-29)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:443
msgid ""
"Severely decreased kidney function. Preparation for kidney replacement "
"therapy (dialysis or transplant) should begin."
msgstr "신장 기능이 심각하게 저하되었습니다. 신장 대체 요법(투석 또는 이식)을 위한 준비가 시작되어야 합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:447
msgid "Stage 5 (eGFR < 15)"
msgstr "5단계(eGFR < 15)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:449
msgid ""
"Kidney failure. Dialysis or kidney transplant is typically needed. Also "
"called end-stage renal disease (ESRD)."
msgstr "신장 장애. 일반적으로 투석이나 신장 이식이 필요합니다. 말기신장질환(ESRD)이라고도 합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:457
msgid "eGFR Formulas Explained"
msgstr "eGFR 공식 설명"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:460
msgid "CKD-EPI Formula"
msgstr "CKD-EPI 공식"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:462
msgid ""
"The preferred formula for calculating eGFR. More accurate than MDRD, "
"especially at higher eGFR levels (above 60). Recommended by most medical "
"organizations."
msgstr ""
"eGFR을 계산하는 데 선호되는 공식입니다. 특히 높은 eGFR 수준(60 이상)에서 MDRD보다 더 정확합니다. 대부분의 의료 기관에서"
" 권장합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:464
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:471
msgid "Takes into account: Creatinine, age, gender, and race"
msgstr "고려 사항: 크레아티닌, 연령, 성별 및 인종"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:467
msgid "MDRD Formula"
msgstr "MDRD 포뮬러"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:469
msgid ""
"An older formula still used for comparison. Less accurate at higher eGFR "
"levels but useful for historical comparison."
msgstr "비교를 위해 여전히 사용되는 오래된 공식입니다. eGFR 수준이 높을수록 정확도가 떨어지지만 과거 비교에는 유용합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:478
msgid "Factors Affecting GFR"
msgstr "GFR에 영향을 미치는 요인"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:480
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:363
msgid "Age:"
msgstr "나이:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:480
msgid ""
"GFR naturally decreases with age. Normal decline is about 1 mL/min/1.73m² "
"per year after age 40."
msgstr "GFR은 나이가 들면서 자연스럽게 감소합니다. 정상적인 감소는 40세 이후 매년 약 1mL/min/1.73m²입니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:481
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:364
msgid "Gender:"
msgstr "성별:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:481
msgid ""
"Men typically have higher muscle mass and creatinine levels, which affects "
"the calculation."
msgstr "남성은 일반적으로 근육량과 크레아티닌 수치가 더 높아 계산에 영향을 미칩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:482
msgid "Race:"
msgstr "경주:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:482
msgid ""
"The formulas include race adjustments based on research showing differences "
"in muscle mass and creatinine production."
msgstr "공식에는 근육량과 크레아티닌 생산의 차이를 보여주는 연구를 기반으로 한 인종 조정이 포함되어 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:483
msgid "Creatinine Level:"
msgstr "크레아티닌 수준:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:483
msgid ""
"Higher creatinine levels indicate reduced kidney function, as kidneys are "
"less able to filter waste from the blood."
msgstr ""
"크레아티닌 수치가 높을수록 신장 기능이 저하되었음을 의미합니다. 신장이 혈액에서 노폐물을 걸러내는 능력이 떨어지기 때문입니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:484
msgid "Muscle Mass:"
msgstr "근육량:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:484
msgid ""
"People with higher muscle mass produce more creatinine, which can affect "
"eGFR calculations."
msgstr "근육량이 많은 사람은 더 많은 크레아티닌을 생성하며 이는 eGFR 계산에 영향을 미칠 수 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:496
msgid ""
"eGFR is an estimate. Actual GFR can only be measured directly through "
"specialized tests. The calculator provides estimates based on standard "
"formulas."
msgstr ""
"eGFR은 추정치입니다. 실제 GFR은 전문적인 검사를 통해서만 직접적으로 측정할 수 있습니다. 계산기는 표준 공식을 기반으로 추정치를 "
"제공합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:502
msgid ""
"eGFR may not be accurate for certain populations, including children, "
"pregnant women, people with very high or low muscle mass, or those with "
"rapidly changing kidney function."
msgstr ""
"eGFR은 어린이, 임산부, 근육량이 매우 높거나 낮은 사람, 신장 기능이 빠르게 변화하는 사람 등 특정 집단에 대해서는 정확하지 않을 "
"수 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:508
msgid ""
"A single eGFR measurement may not be diagnostic. Healthcare providers "
"typically look at trends over time and consider other factors like protein "
"in urine."
msgstr ""
"단일 eGFR 측정으로는 진단이 불가능할 수 있습니다. 의료 서비스 제공자는 일반적으로 시간 경과에 따른 추세를 살펴보고 소변 내 "
"단백질과 같은 다른 요인을 고려합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:514
msgid ""
"This calculator is for educational and informational purposes only. Always "
"consult with healthcare providers for accurate kidney function assessment, "
"diagnosis, and treatment decisions."
msgstr ""
"이 계산기는 교육 및 정보 제공 목적으로만 사용됩니다. 정확한 신장 기능 평가, 진단 및 치료 결정을 위해서는 항상 의료 서비스 제공자와"
" 상담하십시오."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:733
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:839
msgid "mL/min/1.73m²"
msgstr "mL/분/1.73m²"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/gfr_calculator.html:786
msgid "Your Stage"
msgstr "당신의 무대"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:4
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:14
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:23
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:44
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:56
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/views/index.py:22
msgid "Healthy Weight Calculator"
msgstr "건강한 체중 계산기"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:4
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:14
msgid "Calculate Healthy Weight Range"
msgstr "건강한 체중 범위 계산"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:5
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:15
msgid ""
"Calculate your healthy weight range based on BMI categories. Get ideal "
"weight recommendations for your height."
msgstr "BMI 카테고리를 기준으로 건강한 체중 범위를 계산하세요. 귀하의 키에 이상적인 체중 권장 사항을 받아보세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:10
msgid ""
"healthy weight calculator, ideal weight, BMI calculator, weight range, "
"healthy weight range"
msgstr "건강한 체중 계산기, 이상적인 체중, BMI 계산기, 체중 범위, 건강한 체중 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:24
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:59
msgid "Calculate your healthy weight range based on BMI categories."
msgstr "BMI 카테고리를 기준으로 건강한 체중 범위를 계산하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:73
#: Other_Calculators/views/height_calculator.py:818
msgid "Your Height"
msgstr "당신의 키"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:81
msgid "Units"
msgstr "단위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:117
msgid "Range: 3'3"
msgstr "범위: 3'3"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:125
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:486
msgid "Calculate Weight Range"
msgstr "중량 범위 계산"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:155
msgid ""
"Enter your height to see healthy weight ranges based on BMI categories with "
"detailed charts and analysis."
msgstr "자세한 차트와 분석을 통해 BMI 카테고리를 기반으로 건강한 체중 범위를 확인하려면 키를 입력하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:165
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:337
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:380
msgid "Ideal Weight Range"
msgstr "이상적인 체중 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:168
msgid "BMI: 18.5 - 24.9"
msgstr "BMI: 18.5 - 24.9"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:212
msgid "Weight Ranges by BMI"
msgstr "BMI별 체중 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:240
msgid "Weight Range Comparison"
msgstr "중량 범위 비교"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:249
msgid "Weight Ranges by BMI Category"
msgstr "BMI 카테고리별 체중 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:255
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/ideal_weight_calculator.html:187
msgid "BMI Range"
msgstr "BMI 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:256
msgid "Weight Range"
msgstr "중량 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:279
msgid "What is a Healthy Weight?"
msgstr "건강한 체중이란 무엇입니까?"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:281
msgid ""
"A healthy weight is a weight range that is associated with the lowest risk "
"of health problems. It's typically defined using Body Mass Index (BMI), "
"which is a measure of body fat based on height and weight."
msgstr ""
"건강한 체중은 건강 문제의 위험이 가장 낮은 체중 범위입니다. 이는 일반적으로 키와 몸무게를 기준으로 체지방을 측정하는 "
"체질량지수(BMI)를 사용하여 정의됩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:284
msgid ""
"The healthy weight range corresponds to a BMI between 18.5 and 24.9. This "
"range is associated with the lowest risk of developing weight-related health"
" conditions such as heart disease, diabetes, and certain cancers."
msgstr ""
"건강한 체중 범위는 BMI 18.5~24.9에 해당합니다. 이 범위는 심장병, 당뇨병, 특정 암 등 체중 관련 건강 질환이 발생할 위험이"
" 가장 낮은 것과 관련이 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:290
msgid "BMI Categories Explained"
msgstr "BMI 카테고리 설명"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:293
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/pregnancy_weight_gain_calculator.html:356
msgid "Underweight (BMI < 18.5)"
msgstr "저체중(BMI < 18.5)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:295
msgid ""
"May indicate insufficient body weight for optimal health. Can be associated "
"with nutritional deficiencies, weakened immune system, and bone loss."
msgstr "최적의 건강을 위해서는 체중이 부족함을 나타낼 수 있습니다. 영양 결핍, 면역체계 약화, 뼈 손실과 관련될 수 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:299
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/pregnancy_weight_gain_calculator.html:365
msgid "Normal Weight (BMI 18.5-24.9)"
msgstr "정상 체중(BMI 18.5~24.9)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:301
msgid ""
"Associated with the lowest risk of health problems. This is the ideal weight"
" range for most people."
msgstr "건강 문제의 위험이 가장 낮습니다. 이는 대부분의 사람들에게 이상적인 체중 범위입니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:305
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/pregnancy_weight_gain_calculator.html:374
msgid "Overweight (BMI 25-29.9)"
msgstr "과체중(BMI 25-29.9)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:307
msgid ""
"May increase the risk of developing health problems such as high blood "
"pressure, type 2 diabetes, and heart disease."
msgstr "고혈압, 제2형 당뇨병, 심장병과 같은 건강 문제가 발생할 위험이 높아질 수 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:311
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/pregnancy_weight_gain_calculator.html:383
msgid "Obese (BMI ≥ 30)"
msgstr "비만(BMI ≥ 30)"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:313
msgid ""
"Significantly increases the risk of serious health problems including heart "
"disease, stroke, type 2 diabetes, certain cancers, and sleep apnea."
msgstr "심장병, 뇌졸중, 제2형 당뇨병, 특정 암, 수면 무호흡증 등 심각한 건강 문제의 위험을 크게 증가시킵니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:324
msgid "Enter your height in centimeters (cm) or feet and inches"
msgstr "신장을 센티미터(cm) 또는 피트와 인치로 입력하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:325
msgid "Click 'Calculate Weight Range' to see your results"
msgstr "결과를 보려면 '체중 범위 계산'을 클릭하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:326
msgid "Review your ideal weight range and all BMI category ranges"
msgstr "이상적인 체중 범위와 모든 BMI 카테고리 범위를 검토하세요"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:327
msgid ""
"Use the charts to visualize weight ranges across different BMI categories"
msgstr "차트를 사용하여 다양한 BMI 카테고리의 체중 범위를 시각화하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:328
msgid "Refer to the guide below for more information about healthy weight"
msgstr "건강한 체중에 대한 자세한 내용은 아래 가이드를 참조하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:339
msgid ""
"The weight range corresponding to a BMI between 18.5 and 24.9. This is "
"considered the healthy weight range for your height and is associated with "
"the lowest health risks."
msgstr ""
"BMI 18.5~24.9에 해당하는 체중 범위입니다. 이는 키에 따른 건강한 체중 범위로 간주되며 건강 위험이 가장 낮습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:343
msgid "Weight Ranges by Category"
msgstr "카테고리별 체중 범위"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:345
msgid ""
"The calculator shows weight ranges for all BMI categories: Underweight, "
"Normal, Overweight, and Obese. These ranges help you understand where your "
"current weight falls and what your target weight range should be."
msgstr ""
"계산기는 저체중, 정상, 과체중, 비만 등 모든 BMI 범주의 체중 범위를 표시합니다. 이 범위는 현재 체중이 어느 정도 떨어지는지, "
"목표 체중 범위가 무엇인지 이해하는 데 도움이 됩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:349
msgid "BMI Calculation"
msgstr "BMI 계산"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:351
msgid ""
"BMI is calculated using the formula: BMI = weight (kg) / height (m)². The "
"calculator uses this formula to determine weight ranges for each BMI "
"category based on your height."
msgstr ""
"BMI는 BMI = 체중(kg) / 신장(m)² 공식을 사용하여 계산됩니다. 계산기는 이 공식을 사용하여 키를 기준으로 각 BMI "
"카테고리의 체중 범위를 결정합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:359
msgid "Factors Affecting Healthy Weight"
msgstr "건강한 체중에 영향을 미치는 요인"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:361
msgid "Height:"
msgstr "키:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:361
msgid ""
"Taller individuals naturally weigh more than shorter individuals. The "
"calculator adjusts weight ranges based on your height."
msgstr "키가 큰 개인은 키가 작은 개인보다 자연적으로 체중이 더 많이 나갑니다. 계산기는 키에 따라 체중 범위를 조정합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:362
msgid "Body Composition:"
msgstr "신체 구성:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:362
msgid ""
"Muscle weighs more than fat. Athletes with high muscle mass may have a "
"higher BMI but still be healthy."
msgstr "근육은 지방보다 무게가 더 나갑니다. 근육량이 많은 운동선수는 BMI가 더 높을 수 있지만 여전히 건강합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:363
msgid ""
"Metabolism changes with age. Older adults may need to adjust their weight "
"goals based on health conditions and activity levels."
msgstr "신진대사는 나이에 따라 변합니다. 노인들은 건강 상태와 활동 수준에 따라 체중 목표를 조정해야 할 수도 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:364
msgid ""
"Men and women have different body compositions. Men typically have more "
"muscle mass, which affects healthy weight ranges."
msgstr "남성과 여성은 신체 구성이 다릅니다. 남성은 일반적으로 근육량이 더 많아 건강한 체중 범위에 영향을 미칩니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:365
msgid "Health Conditions:"
msgstr "건강 상태:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:365
msgid ""
"Certain medical conditions may require different weight targets. Always "
"consult with healthcare providers for personalized recommendations."
msgstr ""
"특정 건강 상태에는 다른 체중 목표가 필요할 수 있습니다. 개인화된 권장 사항을 얻으려면 항상 의료 서비스 제공자와 상담하십시오."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:371
msgid "Tips for Maintaining a Healthy Weight"
msgstr "건강한 체중 유지를 위한 팁"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:373
msgid ""
"Eat a variety of nutrient-dense foods including fruits, vegetables, whole "
"grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats."
msgstr "과일, 야채, 통곡물, 저지방 단백질, 건강한 지방 등 영양이 풍부한 다양한 음식을 섭취하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:374
msgid ""
"Aim for at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise per week, "
"including both cardio and strength training."
msgstr "유산소 운동과 근력 운동을 모두 포함하여 일주일에 최소 150분의 중간 강도의 운동을 목표로 하세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:375
msgid "Portion Control:"
msgstr "부분 조절:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:375
msgid ""
"Be mindful of portion sizes and avoid overeating. Use smaller plates and "
"listen to your body's hunger cues."
msgstr "섭취량에 주의하고 과식을 피하십시오. 더 작은 접시를 사용하고 신체의 배고픔 신호에 귀를 기울이십시오."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:377
msgid "Get Enough Sleep:"
msgstr "충분한 수면을 취하세요:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:377
msgid ""
"Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep per night. Poor sleep can affect hormones"
" that regulate appetite."
msgstr "매일 밤 7~9시간의 양질의 수면을 목표로 하세요. 잠이 부족하면 식욕을 조절하는 호르몬에 영향을 미칠 수 있습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:378
msgid "Manage Stress:"
msgstr "스트레스 관리:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:378
msgid ""
"Chronic stress can lead to emotional eating and weight gain. Find healthy "
"ways to manage stress."
msgstr "만성 스트레스는 감정적인 식사와 체중 증가로 이어질 수 있습니다. 스트레스를 관리하는 건강한 방법을 찾아보세요."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:390
msgid ""
"BMI is a screening tool, not a diagnostic tool. It doesn't directly measure "
"body fat or account for muscle mass, bone density, or body composition."
msgstr "BMI는 진단 도구가 아닌 선별 도구입니다. 체지방을 직접 측정하거나 근육량, 골밀도 또는 신체 구성을 고려하지 않습니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:396
msgid ""
"The healthy weight range is a general guideline. Individual factors such as "
"muscle mass, bone structure, and health conditions should be considered."
msgstr "건강한 체중 범위는 일반적인 지침입니다. 근육량, 뼈 구조, 건강 상태 등 개별적인 요인을 고려해야 합니다."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:402
msgid ""
"If you're outside the healthy weight range, consult with healthcare "
"providers or registered dietitians for personalized weight management "
"strategies."
msgstr "건강한 체중 범위를 벗어나는 경우, 맞춤형 체중 관리 전략에 대해 의료 서비스 제공자 또는 등록 영양사와 상담하세요."

